						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the temple of Śrī Veṅkatēśvara (also called Sātāni maṭha).</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of the western <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Gōpinātha temple at Rājamahēndra nagara and a gift of a flower garden to the temple by Bhīma, the sister's son of Māreḷḷa Annaya Mantri and son of Kanumūri Annaya and grandson of Mācha Prabhu. In characters of the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
